Here is the balm for every strife,
   Here the sweet mallow grows,
In the wild woods together, free,
   In lovely mottled glows.
The breeze that stirs the lofty boughs —
   The light embossed on stones;
The peace of heart from the forest finds
   A home in human tones—

- John Muir
